reviews.review_text:
set 2 only marcus only taped the second set since a tape flip would be impossible w/ the stealth recording 

http://db.etree.org/shninfo_detail.php?shnid=30699 

this is a matrix of set 2 only, too bad you can only stream it here, look around you'll find it to torrent.
nice set just enjoying my sunday morning coffee listening to this set...a fire scarlet jam with a side of dark star nice.....

3 Minutes of Pure Raw Dead The Kesey eulogy of Bill Graham is extremely overpowering and makes me cry every time. You can feel the raw energy from Ken's voice, and the background music is a very jazzy-free form jam with a lot of power behind it. It's just under 3 minutes, but there's a short window that feels like the quintessential raw power that only the Dead could deliver, ala 1967-1971.

WHAT A SHOW !!!!!!!!!!!! From start to finisnh this show has magic just flowing out the speakers. The help-slip franklin starts it off and what a way to start the night phil droppin bombs left and right it just makes you feel       like your going to blow out the speaks.Also scarlet- fire just makes you want to just get up and dance dance dance the truckin made you just want to sing every word to the song the dark start thourh dark star is just filled with trippy sounds done by the boys  and to rap the evening the werewolves of london was the best way to end the crazy night of great and powerful music the boys did in the there last few years so if you can some how find a copy of the show its a must have in the collection.

Sharing is okay, Bubba. ...so it is my understanding that all grateful dead shows cannot not be downloaded in mp3 format - Or any format for that matter. And that,friends, is total bullshit. 

Sharing incredible music never killed anyone and its not like the Dead cant afford it after all these years.

This show isnt a monumental one at all to say the least but one should be able to enjoy this and all shows in their car or anywhere a CD can be appreciated.

All the Heads went stiff! One of the most memorable shows I ever saw, I recall when Ken Keezy began rapping the halls never been so empty and the seating never so crowded! The place was bursting with stiff Heads trying to hear what was going on, the entire show along with the other 3 days of music were some of my best ever! Long live the DEAD!
Big, fat, juicy and Dead. Sizzling.

WOW!! Immediately my favourite.

The beginning of the second set placing all their perfect improv songs packed together will make anyone keep dancing no matter how thirsty you get!!
